{
  "texts": [
    "The major advantages of the proposed GBSO-TAENN technique are high classification accuracy, reduced computational complexity, increased efficacy, reduced overfitting, and better prediction performance.",
    "Moreover, an advanced deep learning mechanism is utilized for classification, where the hyper-parameters like drop, decay, leaving, and cosine learning are computed for computing the loss function.",
    "Then, this value can be utilized for training the classifier, and it also helps reduce the classification system's complexity.",
    "The EEG signal preprocessing is one of the essential stage in medical diagnosing systems, where the noise/artifacts removal is performed for de-noising the signal.",
    "In this stage, the signal decomposition is mainly performed to reduce the complexity of input EEG signals, which also helps to improve both the detection and classification performance rate."
  ]
}